00:24:57,900 --> 00:25:00,900
lest I should be exalted above measure.

520
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:03,100
Then notice what Paul says in verse number eight.

521
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:04,740
For this thing,

522
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:08,860
I besought the Lord thrice,

523
00:25:08,860 --> 00:25:12,580
that it might depart from me.

524
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:16,820
And Paul was consistent,

525
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:18,000
fervent, if you will.

526
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:21,780
He says I besought the Lord thrice,

527
00:25:21,780 --> 00:25:23,000
that it might depart from me.

528
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:27,640
Now, could God have caused this to depart from him?

529
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,860
He can do anything.

530
00:25:29,980 --> 00:25:32,460
Paul is the one that God used to write

531
00:25:32,460 --> 00:25:34,340
that wonderful promise in Ephesians three,

532
00:25:34,340 --> 00:25:35,340
now unto him,

533
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:36,980
which is able to do exceeding abundantly

534
00:25:36,980 --> 00:25:39,000
above all that we ask or think.

535
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:45,100
But notice what God says in verse number nine,

536
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:47,140
God's answer to Paul,

537
00:25:47,140 --> 00:25:49,500
when Paul besought the Lord

538
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:52,980
with regard to this thorn in the flesh,

539
00:25:52,980 --> 00:25:57,980
God said my grace is sufficient for thee.

540
00:25:57,980 --> 00:26:00,680
My grace is sufficient for thee.

541
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:07,060
For my strength is made perfect in weakness.

542
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:12,740
You know, most of us don't physically,

543
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:16,200
we don't emotionally,

544
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:20,240
we don't want to show any vulnerabilities of weakness.

545
00:26:21,820 --> 00:26:22,660
Right?

546
00:26:22,660 --> 00:26:25,480
We don't want that to be perceived by others

547
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,700
that there's some measure of weakness,

548
00:26:28,540 --> 00:26:33,540
but God says that his strength is made perfect in weakness.

549
00:26:33,540 --> 00:26:38,540
He says my grace is sufficient for thee.

550
00:26:39,780 --> 00:26:42,220
God is no respecter of persons.

551
00:26:43,100 --> 00:26:46,620
And if God's grace was sufficient for Paul,

552
00:26:46,620 --> 00:26:49,360
God's grace is sufficient for every one of us.

553
00:26:50,620 --> 00:26:52,620
And we recognize a healthy church,

554
00:26:52,620 --> 00:26:53,660
and remember a healthy church

555
00:26:53,660 --> 00:26:55,740
is made up of healthy individuals.

556
00:26:55,740 --> 00:26:57,740
I mean, a church is made up of people.

557
00:26:57,740 --> 00:26:59,660
The church is not the building, it's the people.

558
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:02,740
The people are saved and baptized individuals

559
00:27:02,740 --> 00:27:03,880
that make up the church,

560
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:06,860
and a healthy church is going to acknowledge

561
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:10,700
their need for the grace of God, for God's grace.

562
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:13,340
Paul says this after he receives the answer

563
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:15,600
that God gives at the end of verse number nine,

564
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:20,600
most gladly therefore will I rather glory

565
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:25,680
in my infirmities that the power of Christ

566
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:27,840
may rest upon me.

567
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,880
Therefore, notice what he says,

568
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:33,760
I take pleasure in infirmities,

569
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:36,920
in reproaches, in necessities,

570
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:41,920
in persecutions, in distresses for Christ's sake.

571
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:47,460
For when I am weak, then am I strong.

572
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:49,560
What is it in that moment of weakness

573
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:50,960
that would make someone strong?

574
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:53,360
It's the grace of God.

575
00:27:53,360 --> 00:27:55,160
It's God's strength,

576
00:27:55,160 --> 00:28:00,080
his strength being made perfect in our weakness

577
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:04,240
because his grace is sufficient.

578
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:07,800
This evening, a healthy church is a unified church.

579
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:12,040
No schisms, no divisions, a unified church.

580
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:15,440
Unified because we have no differences

581
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:17,580
of background, of personalities.

582
00:28:17,580 --> 00:28:22,580
No, unified because we embrace the same truth.

583
00:28:23,260 --> 00:28:25,820
We accept and we believe the same truth

584
00:28:25,820 --> 00:28:28,660
and therefore God gives us unity.

585
00:28:29,740 --> 00:28:33,500
A healthy church places a priority on the scriptures.

586
00:28:33,500 --> 00:28:36,100
It's God's word that must be taught

587
00:28:36,100 --> 00:28:39,580
and preached and believed, practiced.

588
00:28:39,580 --> 00:28:42,500
As a Baptist, we often will say

589
00:28:42,500 --> 00:28:46,580
that the Bible is our sole authority

590
00:28:46,580 --> 00:28:49,940
for faith and practice.

591
00:28:49,940 --> 00:28:51,760
Well, if the Bible is our sole authority

592
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:53,280
for faith and practice,

593
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:56,640
there must be a priority placed upon the scriptures.

594
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:58,679
It must be taught, it must be learned,

595
00:28:58,679 --> 00:29:01,000
it must be understood, it must be applied.

596
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,119
And so we find that a healthy church

597
00:29:03,119 --> 00:29:04,520
places a priority in the scriptures.

598
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:06,540
And number three, these three elements

599
00:29:06,540 --> 00:29:08,679
that we see in these three concluding verses

600
00:29:08,679 --> 00:29:11,080
is that a healthy church acknowledges

601
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:13,119
their need for God's grace.

602
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,239
By the grace of God, I am what I am.

603
00:29:16,239 --> 00:29:19,559
Where would we be without God's grace?

604
00:29:19,559 --> 00:29:21,600
We must acknowledge that we need God's grace

605
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:24,320
every day of our lives.

606
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:26,720
And I'm thankful that God's grace is sufficient,

607
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,400
that God gives it.

608
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:31,400
I know I said this a number of weeks ago,

609
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:33,720
but sometimes if we're not careful,

610
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:38,720
we can play these hypothetical mind games.

611
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,840
And we can put ourselves in a position of,

612
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:45,220
man, I don't know how I could ever handle such and such.

613
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:48,080
Maybe you hear of someone that has suffered,

614
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:53,080
has experienced some tragedy or some just adversity.

615
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:56,359
And you say, I don't know how I could handle that.

616
00:29:56,359 --> 00:29:58,320
The reality is that we should not play

617
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,119
those hypothetical type of mind.

618
00:30:00,119 --> 00:30:07,679
games because God gives us His grace in the moment that we deal with whatever we deal

619
00:30:07,679 --> 00:30:09,599
with.

620
00:30:09,599 --> 00:30:16,259
And we don't have to think about how could we ever, no, no, we trust that God will give

621
00:30:16,259 --> 00:30:21,839
us the grace in the very moment that we need His grace.

622
00:30:21,839 --> 00:30:26,799
I don't know if you've ever read Foxe's Book of Martyrs or any portion of it or if you've

623
00:30:26,799 --> 00:30:30,199
read of any martyrs of the faith.

624
00:30:30,199 --> 00:30:36,879
But you'll read of individuals that literally are being burned alive singing the praises

625
00:30:36,879 --> 00:30:38,879
of God.

626
00:30:38,879 --> 00:30:40,719
How?

627
00:30:40,719 --> 00:30:51,599
I can't, no, no, in the moment that we need God's grace, God's grace is sufficient.

628
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:57,719
I believe that's the only way that you could explain those types of testimonies, that you

629
00:30:57,719 --> 00:31:09,639
could explain any of those tragic events outside of the grace of God is sufficient.

630
00:31:09,639 --> 00:31:14,519
And I'm so thankful for that wonderful promise that God has given a healthy church.

631
00:31:14,519 --> 00:31:18,239
Healthy church is made up of healthy believers.

632
00:31:18,239 --> 00:31:24,479
Every believer should have the desire to live their life in such a way that God would

633
00:31:24,479 --> 00:31:25,959
be pleased.

634
00:31:25,959 --> 00:31:32,479
That we could say, as we've used for the title of this series, walk worthy, please God.

635
00:31:32,479 --> 00:31:39,319
What a joy that God has given us the instruction so that we know how we can please Him, how

636
00:31:39,319 --> 00:31:41,759
we ought to walk.

637
00:31:41,759 --> 00:31:45,099
The church in Thessalonica was given this instruction.

638
00:31:45,099 --> 00:31:53,779
God graciously has preserved it for us so that we too today can understand how we can

639
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:56,459
walk worthy and please God.

640
00:31:56,459 --> 00:31:57,459
Let's pray together.

641
00:31:57,459 --> 00:31:58,499
Father, we love you.

